Defendant William Edwardo Roldan in court with attorney Debra J Patterson.  Defendant William Edwardo Roldan in custody.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be five (5) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2-1/2 years with credit for 63 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2-1/2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but IS eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of three (3) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample, unless sample has been previously taken.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for his mental or physical needs; take for as long as deemed medically necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with Jennifer C. or Ciria H.;
 - No contact with the Subway restaurant located at 725 West Layton Blvd., in the city and county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Pay restitution to Jennifer C. in the stipulated amount of $22.50 and to Ciria H. in the stipulated amount of $30.62, before all court costs.  Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs and assessments.  Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, Court ordered monies taken from prison funds not to exceed 25%.  Balance to be paid while on extended supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargeable in bankruptcy.
 - Serve 4 months condition time at the House of Correction, with Huber privileges for work, if employed.  Court would allow good time. 

Filed,
